name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Not slipping back into ‚Äúhigh risk‚Äù ‚Äî depends upon YOU and your continued efforts to stay safe, to stay healthy and to stay strong by exercising great care in your social interactions, and exercising precautionary measures when you are in public.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Let me be exceedingly clear: Moving from HIGH RISK (red) to MODERATE RISK (orange) does NOT mean business as usual.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We identify which level of risk our communities are facing by analyzing a data dashboard, which compares data on hospitalizations, hospital capacity, and testing, to name a few key metrics.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
- RED indicates a HIGH RISK, 
- ORANGE indicates MODERATE RISK, 
- YELLOW would show a LOW RISK, and 
- GREEN indicates what we might call our ‚ÄúNEW NORMAL RISK‚Äù for COVID-19, meaning, even in green, all of us need to exercise caution and care.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Just as impressive as what we have been able to do as institutions is what you have done individually. You are adapting, you are even more self-reliant than we thought. And you are protecting each other.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We have procured over 5 million N95 or KN95 masks, over 4 million surgical gowns, and over half a million face shields. We are continuing to build up these supplies.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We've also been working to increase our medical capacity: We have created isolation and quarantine sites statewide, we have worked with our hospitals to offer a coordinated standard of crisis care.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We have built up a strong contact tracing capacity, with nearly 1200 health officials supporting that effort. They are supported by the Healthy Together app, which you can download from the Apple Store or Google Play.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: With the help of @UofUHealth and ARUP, we are putting in place large-scale prevalence and incidence studies to understand Utah's exposure to COVID-19, as well as focused antibody testing to deploy to healthcare, frontline workers, and critical infrastructure workers.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We have greatly increase our capacity to test and trace for COVID-19. We can currently conduct 6,000 tests per day, and we can do lab work for 9,000 tests per day.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Next week we will provide more information in our press briefings to help better acquaint ourselves with what life under MODERATE RISK, or Orange, will look like.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
The number of new hospitalizations has been declining since April 8, and using our most conservative estimation of the data, has declined by 18% over the last seven days.

We estimate that the transition rate of the virus is near 1 to 1.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
We are not being guided by fear or politics. We will base these decisions off crucial data points, including: 

1) Trends in new hospitalizations (this tells us how the virus is spreading and if it is hitting populations that require high levels of medical intervention).

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
6. Cover coughs or sneezes into the sleeve or elbow,not hands

7. Clean high-touch surfaces (buttons, door handles, counters, etc.) regularly

8. Avoid touching your face

9. Refrain from hand shaking

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
I work with other state officials daily to review key health indicators related to COVID-19 in order to determine the wisdom of adjusting current directives and orders. 

We‚Äôre glad those who need medical procedures are now better able to get the medical attention they need.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Utah has worked hard to establish new and dependable supply chains to provide us with PPE through the crisis. Because of current supplies and close monitoring of demand, we were able to modestly relax standards on elective procedures. We can always dial this back down if needed.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We are also working to support our tribes. This has included providing mobile testing to the Navajo Mountain and Monument Valley areas of the Navajo nation, pushing out Public Health Emergency Preparedness funding to tribal programs and the Urban Indian Center of Salt Lake.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Our Refugee Education and Training Center through @JobsUT has assisted 1,722 individuals in 62 languages since March 30. Refugee Services provides daily email updates to refugees, community leaders, and refugee service providers throughout the state.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
The subcommittee will also include partners from government and business, leaders of faith-based organizations, and community advocates. 

The co-chairs will be Zee Min Xiao, who is on the Utah Multicultural Commission, and Byron Russell, co-chair of the Multicultural Commission.
